http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Enrolment-drive-launched/article14000677.ece

A drive was launched to extend benefits of various Union government schemes to casual workers and street vendors under the Bharath Informal Workers Initiative (BIWI), here on Thursday.The objective is to bring unorganised sector workers under the social security network and extend benefits such as health insurance, health security, and skill development programme for the children of such workers. It also emphasises on extending financial assistance to pushcart and roadside vendors. The drive was launched by former minister S.A. Ramdas. Speaking on the occasion, he said that about 5,000 workers, including autorickshaw drivers, masons, fruit and vegetable vendors, and others would be registered during the drive to avail benefits. The drive began at 5.30 a.m.